div.p: Continue building out the Bolt Network project, which you started here. Bolt Network wants to add more shows to their program page. Here's what it looks like.

div.span: Mark the tasks as complete by checking them off

div.p: Make a new folder js/directives/. Inside this folder, create a file js/directives/programListing.js. In this file,create a new directive named programListing:

ul.li: Use app.directive to create the new directive
Use restrict to create a new Element
Use scope to specify that we'll pass information into this directive through an attribute named listing
Use templateUrl to tell this directive to use the js/directives/programListing.html file

div.p: Include this new JavaScript file in the view as a <script> element.
Next, write the directive's template. Make a new file js/directives/programListing.html. Move the HTML from index.html inside the .content div into the directive's template file.

The programListing directive takes in information through the listing attribute. The data in listing becomes available to use in the directive's template. Update the expressions in the directive's template so that it uses listing to display each item.
In the view, use the <program-listing> directive to display the details of program.
Add another object to the controller. Feel free to use your favorite TV show.
Use another <program-listing> directive to display the details of the new object.

div.span: If you see a bug or any other issue with this page, please report it

div.p: The panel on the left shows all the folders and files included in your root directory. Select a file from the left in order to preview and/or open it.
